results.abstract: Lt Col Leonov says his movements during 'space walk' caused Voskhod to begin rotating, apparently like Gemini 8
results.snippet: MOSCOW, March 18 (UPI)  Aleksei Leonov, the Soviet cosmonaut who was the first man to float in space outside his spacecraft, said today that his movements had caused his six-ton Voskhod spacecraft to begin rotating unexpectedly.
